
# Help

## How to download a word cloud
Note that both allow saves in the .png format

## Modern
1. Go to the modern version (see below) 
![download image](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanyagupta/li60/master/images/modern_initial.png)
1. You can now download the cloud by clicking on the download icon (see below). This will save it in  your local downloads folder
![download image](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanyagupta/li60/master/images/wc_modern_click2download.png)

## Classic
In the classic version, when you run the cloud click on "make downloadable"
![download image](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanyagupta/li60/master/images/wc_make_downloadable.png)

1. You will see the following screen
![download image](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanyagupta/li60/master/images/wc_make_editable.png)
1.  Then go on top of word cloud, right click and save as
![download image](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanyagupta/li60/master/images/wc_classic_save_as.png)
1.  Give a name to your word cloud. This will save it to a location of your choice on your computer
